name: Daniel
analysis: Nebius is capitalizing on the explosive growth in AI inference, which is projected to account for two-thirds of compute workloads. Hyperscalers such as Microsoft and Meta, constrained by global compute shortages amid a rapidly expanding data center market, are increasingly relying on Nebius for dedicated capacity through multi-billion-dollar contracts. Nebius projects $7–9 billion in annual recurring revenue for 2026, a dramatic increase from $551 million in 2025.
